# Pre-commit and Ruff (recommended before every commit)

Before committing or opening a PR, ensure the **pre-commit** bundle passes. The **CI** **Lint** job runs **`uv run pre-commit run --all-files`** — the same hooks as **`.pre-commit-config.yaml`**.

## Setup (one-time per clone)

```bash
uv sync
uv run pre-commit install
```

## What runs (commit or `pre-commit run --all-files`)

- **Ruff** check (`--fix`) and **Ruff format** (`--check`) — config in `pyproject.toml`.
- **plans-stats** — `python scripts/plans-stats.py --check` (dashboard must match `PLANS_TODO.md`).
- **plans-hub** — `python scripts/plans_hub_sync.py --check` (generated table in `PLANS_HUB.md` must match all `PLAN_*.md` files).
- **Markdown lint**, **pt-BR locale**, **confidential commercial** guards (pytest).

Manual run on all files:

```bash
uv run pre-commit run --all-files
```

## When suggesting or reviewing changes

- **Recommend** **`uv run pre-commit run --all-files`** (or installed hooks) before push so **CI Lint** stays green.
- If **ruff-format** fails: **`uv run ruff format .`** and re-stage.
- Do not bypass checks with **`--no-verify`** unless intentional; keep **`.pre-commit-config.yaml`** aligned with **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`** **lint** job.

## Other lint

Broader quality layers: **`docs/QUALITY_WORKFLOW_RECOMMENDATIONS.md`**, **Bandit**, **Semgrep**, **CodeQL** (separate CI jobs or workflows).
